http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/%E2%80%98Sustained-agitation-need-of-the-hour%E2%80%99/article14636408.ece

A sustained agitation till the Centre announced a new railway zone with headquarters in Visakhapatnam is the need of the hour, opined the speakers at a meeting held here on Sunday.They said the BJP and TDP leaders were issuing statements that they were in favour of Visakhapatnam as the headquarters of the zone but both the parties had their own reasons to favour Vijayawada. Railway Zone Sadhana Samithi convener J.V. Satyanarayana Murthy says: “Odisha is also objecting to Polavaram and other water projects, which would bring prosperity to AP. Will the government stop construction of these projects”?YSR Congress district president Gudivada Amarnath alleged that the ruling parties were trying to cheat the people by raking up non-issues.INTUC leader Mantri Rajasekhar accused the Centre was trying to create a rift between the people of two regions in the State by promising to establish the headquarters in Visakhapatnam and now having second thoughts.Uttarandhra Rakshana Vedika president S.S. Siva Shankar said agitation for the zone would be intensified and spread to all regions of the State from Sept. 14.